sent: august 13, 2020from: vincent j. del casino, jr., provost and senior vp for academic affairsdear colleagues,as we approach the start of the fall semester, we are excited to see the creativity that you have brought to rethinking and redesigning your courses for an online environment. we know that you have been working hard to develop an excellent remote teaching and learning experience for all of our students. they will benefit immensely from your efforts.in accordance with guidance from the csu chancellors office, we are providing additionalonline learning syllabus guidance for fall 2020. a set offaqs and resourceson remote proctoring and alternate assessments for faculty is also provided. faculty are encouraged to consider alternate assessments, issues of equity and privacy, and necessary disability accommodations in a virtual environment.these documents provide suggested syllabus language on topics such as zoom privacy and online proctoring. we also encourage you to review thebest practices information on academic integrityin online courses provided on theteach anywheresite.information on these topics is also available for students in the faqs area of thelearn anywheresite.sincerely,vinphone:408-924-2400email:provost@sjsu.educlark hall 552one washington squaresan jos, ca 95192-0020